      <reaction compartment="compartment_70101" fast="false" id="reaction_909718" metaid="metaid_102" name="Formation of p-STAT1 homodimer" reversible="false">
        <notes>
          <p xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">Under certain conditions type I IFNs, IFNA/B are able to activate genes through a second STAT-based signaling cascade enabling the formation of p-STAT1:p-STAT1 homodimers called IFNA-activated-factor (AAF).</p>
        </notes>
        <annotation>
