      <reaction compartment="compartment_13231" fast="false" id="reaction_909721" metaid="metaid_112" name="Translocation of ISGF3 complex to nucleus" reversible="false">
        <notes>
          <p xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">The resultant ISGF3 trimeric complex then migrates to the nucleus and binds to interferon-stimulated response elements (ISREs). IRF9 is the DNA binding part of this ISGF3 complex. These ISREs are present in the promoters of a subset of ISGs (interferon stimulated genes), such as promyelocytic leukemia (PML), ISG15 ubiquitin-like modifier (ISG15), interferon-induced protein with tetratricopeptide repeats 2 (ISG54) and interferon alpha-inducible protein 6 (IFI6) to elicit an antiviral response.</p>
        </notes>
        <annotation>
          <rdf:RDF xmlns:rdf="http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/" xmlns:vCard="http://www.w3.org/2001/vcard-rdf/3.0#" xmlns:dcterms="http://purl.org/dc/terms/" xmlns:bqbiol="http://biomodels.net/biology-qualifiers/">
