      <reaction compartment="compartment_876" fast="false" id="reaction_909724" metaid="metaid_115" name="Recruitment of IFNAR1" reversible="false">
        <notes>
          <p xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">The extracellular domain of IFNAR1 is atypical, consisting of a tandem array of four FNIII domains and the first three N-terminal FNIII domains are involved in ligand recognition. IFNAR1 is recruited to the binary complex (IFNA/B:IFNAR2) on the membrane to form the ternary complex (IFNAR2:IFNA/B:IFNAR1). TYK2 kinase is pre-associated with IFNAR1 and JAK1 with IFNAR2. The binding of IFNA/B to IFNA receptors brings these JAK kinase together, allowing cross-phosphorylation and kinase activation.</p>
        </notes>
        <annotation>
          <rdf:RDF xmlns:rdf="http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/" xmlns:vCard="http://www.w3.org/2001/vcard-rdf/3.0#" xmlns:dcterms="http://purl.org/dc/terms/" xmlns:bqbiol="http://biomodels.net/biology-qualifiers/">
